Sainsbury's is taking over Boots, Superdrug and Debenhams and filling them with supermarket-like stores filled with beauty and cosmetics and managed by experts in the field.
As part of a major breakthrough in the UK's £2.8 billion beauty market, which continues to grow while fashion and home goods sales are falling, wider ranges of beauty products will be trialled in 11 stores and applied to others if the experiment proves successful.
